50|$|In the Reformed tradition, which {{stresses}} <b>preaching</b> as {{a central}} concern, pastors often don <b>preaching</b> tabs, which project from their clerical collar. <b>Preaching</b> bands (an alternative name for tabs) are also worn by Anglican clergy, particularly on occasions such as inductions when choir dress of cassock, surplice, <b>preaching</b> scarf and the academic hood pertaining to degree is worn, {{as well as at}} Mattins and Evensong. Methodist and Lutheran clergy also sometimes attach <b>preaching</b> bands to their clerical collars.|$|R
